description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 9:00- 10:00pm No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Must have completed Fundamentals or have instructor permission to attend. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

Auditioned performance groups with rehearsals twice a week plus additional class and social requirements. The group has performed locally as well as in Puerto Rico, New York, Atlanta, Seattle and Chicago. By audition only. Open to team members by audition only. Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description: We are excited to bring you dancing at an all ages venue right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 7:45pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:00pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:00pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. All ages welcome. $15.00 per person + service fee on Eventbrite or cash only at the door. $13 cash for Edelweiss Club members at the door only. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: Victoria Edelweiss Club, 108 Niagara St, Victoria, BC V8V 1E9, Canada

description: We are excited to bring you dancing the 2nd Saturday of every month right in the heart of downtown, with a wooden dance floor!!!!! 8:15pm Doors open Salsa Caliente’s team will be there to greet you. 8:30pm Salsa lesson Taught by World Salsa University certified instructor, Christina Morrison. No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson so you will already know a LOT of people by the time the dancing begins. 9:30pm- midnight Dancing to Salsa, Bachata, Merengue, Cha Cha Cha and more. Ages 16+ welcome. CASH ONLY at the door. $15.00 per person. Tickets available at the door or on Eventbrite . There will be a small non-alcoholic concession available as a fundraiser for the teams. *Limited capacity. First come first served. We reserve the right to refuse entrance at the door.
location: STUDIO 4 ATHLETICS, 715 YATES ST,  BC, V8W 1L6, CA

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

Join us every Thursday for Kizomba/Urbankiz classes at the Ukrainian Cultural Centre. The event on 20 March 2025 runs from 19:30 to 22:30, featuring intermediate sessions (7:30PM-8:15PM) and beginner sessions (8:15PM-9:00PM), followed by a practica until 10:30PM. Pricing options include Class only: $10; Class & Practica: $15 (or $10 for university students with ID). Event organized by David Lamine, Victoria Kizomba Lovers Group, and others.
location: Ukrainian Cultural Centre, 3277 Douglas St, Victoria, British Columbia

dance_style: line dance, swing, west coast swing
description: Canada's largest and longest running Country, West Coast Swing and Line Dance event featuring international dance competitions, over 110 instructional workshops, multiple evening social dance rooms, a Campfire Ball Showcase and Seated Dinner, plus extended social dancing. Event organized by Calgary Dance Stampede and Keith Armbruster.
location: Hyatt Regency Calgary, 700 Centre St S, Calgary, Alberta,  BC, T2G 5P6, CA

event_name: Saturday Lesson and Dance at Eastern Star Hall
description: Event includes a drop-in beginner lesson from 7-8 pm and social dancing from 8-10:15. Doors open at 6:45 pm. Cost $12. Please bring low heeled, scuff-free shoes or socks and a water bottle. Event by Donna Forsyth and Victoria West Coast Swing Collective.
location: Eastern Star Hall Chapters No 5 & No 17, 3281 Harriet Rd, Victoria, British Columbia,  BC, V8Z 3S3, CA

event_name: Vancouver Bachata Sensual Weekend - Next Edition
description: WE ARE BACK AGAIN Get ready for the next edition of Vancouver Bachata Sensual Weekend! Enjoy an exceptional gaming experience and three unique dining experiences.
source: Vancouver bachata Sensual Weekend - Next Edition
location: Cascades Casino Delta, 6005 BC-17A, Delta,  BC, V4K 5B8, CA

event_name: Rx: Vancouver Easter Swing Ticket Tournament
description: Join Rx on Saturday March 22nd for their fourth Easter Swing Ticket Tournament featuring a social dance from 6:30pm to 11pm. Early bird registration ends March 1st, and there are competition divisions for newcomer/novice and intermediate/advanced dancers with exciting prizes.
source: Vancouver West Coast Swing Community | Facebook
location: 2474 Prince Edward St, Vancouver, BC V5T 3M8, Canada

event_name: Sunday Sundown Social: Leprechaun Latin Dance Night
description: Celebrate St. Patrick’s Day with an evening of Latin social dancing featuring a beginner dance lesson and social dancing. Enjoy styles such as salsa, bachata, kizomba, and merengue. Part of the monthly series held on the last Sunday of every month from September to May. Dress in green for a chance to win a raffle prize.
location: 111 Superior St, Victoria, BC V8V 1T2, Canada

event_name: Bailabeat Returns to Bimini’s – Where It All Began!
description: Bailabeat is coming home! Featuring a Bachata lesson from 18:00 to 18:30 with no partner needed followed by a social dance party with salsa, bachata, and merengue from 18:30 to 22:30. Celebrate the legacy of Bailabeat at Bimini’s.
source: Vancouver bachata Sensual Weekend - Next Edition
location: Bimini’s, Vancouver, BC,  BC, V6J 1M9, CA

description: Dance until 1 am! Wear your best clothes to show off a completely 70s outfit.

dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is perfect for brand new beginners, dancers of other styles, or more experienced dancers that want to continue to improve technique. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Tuesday from 8:00- 9:00pm No experience or partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

description:
Rehearsal for our Student Salsa Team. Open to team members only. Team Description
Local all levels performance group with rehearsals once a week. If you have never performed before or have a limited amount of time you are able to commit to, this is the team for you. Learn exciting choreographies to perform at local events with no pressure to perform until you are ready. Open to team members only. No dance experience, partner or audition required! Please email director@calientedance.com or call 250-881-6141 for information on how to join the team. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition.
location: 725 Yates ST, VICTORIA, BC, V8W1L6, CA

event_name: Salsa On 2 & Cha Cha Cha - Intermediate/ Advanced
dance_style: cha cha, cha cha cha, salsa
description: Class Description This class is for experienced dancers and performers that want to continue to push themselves with more complex techniques. NY Style Salsa (Mambo) is danced to the rhythm of the congas and the techniques used allow for quick turns and direction changes, complex partner patterns and more body movement while dancing on a crowded dance floor. Cha Cha Cha is a fun dance with a playful energy that uses a very similar step to Salsa and learning them together will help you understand and be better at both. Every Monday from 8:00- 9:00pm Must have instructor permission to attend. No partner is necessary as we rotate partners throughout the lesson. Call 250-881-6141 or email info@calientedance.com for more details. * Please arrive no earlier than 5 min before class to allow for smooth class transition. No drop ins permitted so please contact us to reserve your spot!
